1
00:00:06,140 --> 00:00:08,540
=Fireworks=

2
00:00:08,540 --> 00:00:10,860
=Episode 13=

3
00:00:25,519 --> 00:00:28,280
You think getting my resignation letter
means you won?

4
00:00:31,160 --> 00:00:36,679
Get ready for the ultimate gift
I'm sending you.

5
00:00:37,159 --> 00:00:41,240
It's time for your exit.

6
00:00:48,180 --> 00:00:51,340
(Song Che:
Ms. Qiao, got time for a chat?)

7
00:00:54,359 --> 00:00:57,079
What can I do for you, Mr. Song?

8
00:00:57,479 --> 00:01:00,280
The batch of goods sent to Song Group
has quality issues.

9
00:01:00,399 --> 00:01:01,600
I need to verify the order.

10
00:01:02,960 --> 00:01:05,799
That's impossible.
I checked everything before shipping.

11
00:01:05,799 --> 00:01:07,040
There were no issues at all.

12
00:01:07,519 --> 00:01:10,319
The product inspection
has shown poor quality.

13
00:01:13,160 --> 00:01:14,159
How do you explain this?

14
00:01:17,359 --> 00:01:18,760
(Quality Inspection Report)
If I'm not mistaken,

15
00:01:19,439 --> 00:01:22,480
Qiao Group has recently
been caught in a forgery scandal.

16
00:01:23,640 --> 00:01:25,239
Are you trying to fool me?

17
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:30,319
Sorry, Mr. Song.

18
00:01:30,480 --> 00:01:32,159
Maybe the workers mixed up

19
00:01:32,480 --> 00:01:34,760
the good products
with the defective ones during shipping.

20
00:01:35,760 --> 00:01:37,480
I'll send a replacement right away.

21
00:01:37,480 --> 00:01:39,719
Also, let's sign a new agreement.

22
00:01:39,719 --> 00:01:40,879
I'll send it to your email.

23
00:01:43,879 --> 00:01:46,040
(Qiao Wenjun's sudden change)

24
00:01:46,150 --> 00:01:47,799
(must be because of some hidden agenda.)

25
00:01:48,439 --> 00:01:50,879
(She's not someone
who would show weakness.)

26
00:01:56,079 --> 00:01:58,280
Are you worried about tomorrow?

27
00:02:01,400 --> 00:02:04,200
I've got a bad feeling about this.

28
00:02:05,079 --> 00:02:08,560
Qiao Wenjun is voluntarily
giving up something she's always wanted.

29
00:02:09,560 --> 00:02:11,080
That's hard to believe.

30
00:02:12,319 --> 00:02:13,120
But...

31
00:02:15,280 --> 00:02:16,080
I'll help you win.

32
00:02:20,060 --> 00:02:22,100
(Qiao Group)

33
00:02:22,100 --> 00:02:27,280
(Qiao Group Shareholders Meeting)

34
00:02:27,280 --> 00:02:28,479
Why did Wenjun

35
00:02:28,479 --> 00:02:29,360
suddenly

36
00:02:29,520 --> 00:02:30,759
gather all of us?

37
00:02:30,759 --> 00:02:33,840
- Qiao Nian just got back from abroad.
- Oh.

38
00:02:42,240 --> 00:02:45,240
Everyone, please welcome Ms. Qiao Nian.

39
00:02:57,520 --> 00:02:59,159
She killed Mr. Qiao

40
00:02:59,530 --> 00:03:00,960
and still has the nerve to sit here?

41
00:03:01,240 --> 00:03:02,879
- Yeah.
- Right.

42
00:03:03,240 --> 00:03:04,800
Why's she even here?

43
00:03:08,400 --> 00:03:10,039
Everyone, please calm down.

44
00:03:11,039 --> 00:03:14,439
Thank you for taking the time
to attend this meeting.

45
00:03:15,439 --> 00:03:16,919
Since my father passed,

46
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:19,039
I've been managing the company.

47
00:03:20,319 --> 00:03:21,439
But...

48
00:03:22,400 --> 00:03:25,680
I know this position
has always belonged to Qiao Nian.

49
00:03:25,800 --> 00:03:26,919
(Keep acting.)

50
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:28,580
(Let's see what you're up to this time.)

51
00:03:28,639 --> 00:03:29,639
You two

52
00:03:29,960 --> 00:03:31,599
are the backbone of Qiao Group.

53
00:03:32,360 --> 00:03:34,599
If you both take charge of the company,

54
00:03:34,759 --> 00:03:35,719
Qiao Group

55
00:03:35,719 --> 00:03:38,319
will definitely thrive for a long time.

56
00:03:39,840 --> 00:03:40,840
Right.

57
00:03:41,560 --> 00:03:43,840
Today, I have
another announcement to make.

58
00:03:45,120 --> 00:03:47,759
I'm leaving Qiao Group.

59
00:03:48,400 --> 00:03:49,719
Starting today,

60
00:03:50,240 --> 00:03:53,000
I will officially
step down as chairperson.

61
00:03:55,639 --> 00:03:57,039
That's so sudden.

62
00:03:57,400 --> 00:03:59,759
What happened?

63
00:04:01,120 --> 00:04:03,159
Ms. Qiao, you're leaving?

64
00:04:04,960 --> 00:04:07,759
Qiao Nian is all this company needs.

65
00:04:12,400 --> 00:04:13,400
This is bad.

66
00:04:14,039 --> 00:04:15,719
We're in the middle of a meeting.

67
00:04:16,170 --> 00:04:17,560
We just got a notice from the bank.

68
00:04:17,600 --> 00:04:19,560
Several large sums of money
have been transferred

69
00:04:19,639 --> 00:04:22,079
from our company account
to private accounts,

70
00:04:22,600 --> 00:04:24,199
totaling 300 million.

71
00:04:25,399 --> 00:04:26,439
Look.

72
00:04:26,439 --> 00:04:27,639
The stock price dropped.

73
00:04:27,839 --> 00:04:30,600
The company's funds
are for specific purposes only.

74
00:04:31,600 --> 00:04:33,000
The stock price dropped again.

75
00:04:33,040 --> 00:04:34,199
Who did this?

76
00:04:34,319 --> 00:04:35,759
Yeah, who did it?

77
00:04:36,759 --> 00:04:39,959
We traced the private accounts,
and they're Ms. Qiao Nian's.

78
00:04:42,639 --> 00:04:44,319
I just got back to the company.

79
00:04:44,360 --> 00:04:45,879
I haven't done a single thing,

80
00:04:46,040 --> 00:04:49,079
and now you're accusing me
of embezzling company funds?

81
00:04:50,240 --> 00:04:51,040
Everyone,

82
00:04:51,759 --> 00:04:53,800
don't you think something's off here?

83
00:04:54,720 --> 00:04:56,680
Maybe this happened
while you weren't around.

84
00:04:57,399 --> 00:04:59,839
Yeah. Since Mr. Qiao passed away,

85
00:05:00,199 --> 00:05:03,240
the chairperson's audit powers
have been with you.

86
00:05:03,279 --> 00:05:04,079
Nian,

87
00:05:04,920 --> 00:05:08,319
you've betrayed
every shareholder in this room.

88
00:05:08,720 --> 00:05:10,360
You've betrayed your grandpa.

89
00:05:10,480 --> 00:05:11,279
Qiao Nian,

90
00:05:11,480 --> 00:05:13,439
you've got to explain this to us today.

91
00:05:13,879 --> 00:05:16,120
Give us an explanation.

92
00:05:16,839 --> 00:05:18,920
You're the CFO, right?

93
00:05:22,079 --> 00:05:24,319
If you want to keep your job,

94
00:05:24,759 --> 00:05:25,800
you'd better tell us.

95
00:05:26,279 --> 00:05:28,279
Who told you to slander me?

96
00:05:29,120 --> 00:05:32,120
Otherwise, you'll face the consequences.

97
00:05:36,319 --> 00:05:37,240
You can't deny it.

98
00:05:37,800 --> 00:05:38,959
I've got evidence.

99
00:05:40,000 --> 00:05:42,399
If I hadn't checked
this quarter's financial report,

100
00:05:42,920 --> 00:05:45,120
Qiao Group would have
been ruined by your hands.

101
00:05:46,439 --> 00:05:48,279
We'd all be in trouble because of you.

102
00:05:48,360 --> 00:05:49,480
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

103
00:05:50,000 --> 00:05:50,800
Really?

104
00:05:52,560 --> 00:05:53,680
I've got evidence too.

105
00:05:59,519 --> 00:06:01,240
Mr. Jiang and Mr. Song?

106
00:06:01,639 --> 00:06:03,120
Why are they here?

107
00:06:03,759 --> 00:06:05,759
Everyone, calm down.

108
00:06:07,079 --> 00:06:08,759
I have something to show you.

109
00:06:19,920 --> 00:06:21,519
What? Did you see that?

110
00:06:21,879 --> 00:06:23,600
That's what happened?

111
00:06:23,800 --> 00:06:25,279
Is this for real?

112
00:06:25,330 --> 00:06:26,279
You're really something.

113
00:06:26,439 --> 00:06:27,399
You actually found this?

114
00:06:30,079 --> 00:06:33,439
I noticed unusual movements
in the company's funds three years ago,

115
00:06:33,959 --> 00:06:35,639
so I had someone investigate.

116
00:06:37,240 --> 00:06:39,000
(Did I get caught?)

117
00:06:39,959 --> 00:06:41,360
I found that Qiao Wenjun

118
00:06:42,360 --> 00:06:44,720
was transferring a large amount
of money overseas.

119
00:06:45,240 --> 00:06:47,759
And the source of those funds
was the company's account.

120
00:06:49,240 --> 00:06:52,160
Jiang Zechen, stop throwing dirt on me.

121
00:06:52,560 --> 00:06:54,600
Qiao Nian was the one
who transferred the funds.

122
00:06:54,800 --> 00:06:57,279
Besides, you've already left the company.

123
00:06:57,680 --> 00:07:00,160
How can you still
monitor the company's funds?

124
00:07:01,639 --> 00:07:06,839
Or did Qiao Nian break the contract
and give you the key?

125
00:07:10,439 --> 00:07:12,000
If you don't want anyone to know,

126
00:07:12,759 --> 00:07:14,040
don't do it in the first place.

127
00:07:15,240 --> 00:07:20,079
Ms. Qiao Wenjun, as Qiao Group's
current business partner,

128
00:07:20,720 --> 00:07:22,759
I think I have the right
to know the truth.

129
00:07:23,200 --> 00:07:25,120
I had someone
secretly intercept these accounts.

130
00:07:26,560 --> 00:07:29,560
I found that the overseas accounts
receiving the funds

131
00:07:29,560 --> 00:07:31,079
are all shell companies.

132
00:07:32,519 --> 00:07:34,519
And the legal representatives
of these companies

133
00:07:34,600 --> 00:07:36,120
are all people from Qiao Wenjun's side

134
00:07:36,879 --> 00:07:39,120
and some of the shareholders here.

135
00:07:40,920 --> 00:07:41,720
Ms. Qiao Wenjun.

136
00:07:43,519 --> 00:07:44,879
Do you have anything to say?

137
00:07:45,680 --> 00:07:46,839
(What should I do?)

138
00:07:47,240 --> 00:07:48,480
(How should I fight back?)

139
00:07:49,839 --> 00:07:51,199
What's going on?

140
00:07:51,439 --> 00:07:52,839
Yeah, that's so much money.

141
00:07:53,000 --> 00:07:53,959
By the way, everyone,

142
00:07:54,519 --> 00:07:55,800
I also have here

143
00:07:55,800 --> 00:07:58,680
a forged order for Dolphi Beauty,

144
00:07:59,199 --> 00:08:02,439
and the signatory
is none other than Qiao Wenjun.

145
00:08:03,319 --> 00:08:04,560
So it's really her.

146
00:08:04,800 --> 00:08:05,639
It's really her.

147
00:08:08,319 --> 00:08:09,199
Song Che.

148
00:08:10,360 --> 00:08:11,519
You played me?

149
00:08:13,560 --> 00:08:18,199
So, Qiao Nian wasn't the one
behind the product forgery?

150
00:08:18,199 --> 00:08:19,000
That's right.

151
00:08:20,040 --> 00:08:20,839
Ms. Qiao.

152
00:08:21,920 --> 00:08:23,560
Do you have anything to say?

153
00:08:24,759 --> 00:08:25,600
The evidence is clear.

154
00:08:27,639 --> 00:08:28,439
Hmph.

155
00:08:28,600 --> 00:08:30,360
You think taking me down

156
00:08:30,759 --> 00:08:34,639
means Qiao Nian
can just take over Qiao Group?

157
00:08:37,120 --> 00:08:38,919
She doesn't even qualify.

158
00:08:39,799 --> 00:08:42,639
She's not even from the Qiao bloodline.

159
00:08:42,799 --> 00:08:44,679
What? How's that possible?

160
00:08:45,080 --> 00:08:46,600
Is this true?

161
00:08:47,700 --> 00:08:49,190
What proof do you have to claim that?

162
00:08:49,360 --> 00:08:51,559
And what proof do you have
to claim she is?

163
00:08:51,879 --> 00:08:53,360
I can prove it.

164
00:08:56,399 --> 00:08:58,080
- Mr. Qiao?
- Mr. Qiao?

165
00:09:01,230 --> 00:09:07,200
♪So many words unsaid,
the deeper we fall, the more we fear♪

166
00:09:07,480 --> 00:09:15,080
♪Fate like a gamble,
locking us inside its game♪

167
00:09:15,130 --> 00:09:18,920
♪Hearts at play, truth and lies,
who could ever know♪

168
00:09:19,440 --> 00:09:22,720
♪Where this ends♪

169
00:09:22,720 --> 00:09:30,000
♪I try to walk away,
yet still step into the fire♪

170
00:09:30,000 --> 00:09:34,330
♪Your heartbeat pulls me under,
and I lose myself♪

171
00:09:34,370 --> 00:09:37,450
♪Love turns into pain♪

172
00:09:37,520 --> 00:09:41,640
♪Words betray us
until our eyes burn red♪

173
00:09:41,800 --> 00:09:45,280
♪Yet I still want you close♪

174
00:09:45,280 --> 00:09:49,450
♪Your tide breaks me,
and I fall for you again♪

175
00:09:49,450 --> 00:09:52,760
♪Even if love becomes nothing♪

176
00:09:52,760 --> 00:09:57,330
♪When love and hate fade
into the crowd and the ice melts♪

177
00:09:57,330 --> 00:10:03,640
♪Does it mean we could meet again?♪

178
00:10:04,230 --> 00:10:08,420
♪Your heartbeat pulls me under,
and I lose myself♪

179
